Subject: Surface Periphery Inquiry Table

Description: Seed lookup table mapping surface-layer inquiry terms to deeper SOP files to search.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SurfacePeripheryInquiryIndex.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SectionedPeripheryAssociationFabric.sop

& [SurfacePeripheryInquiryTable] is the current table for surface-to-depth search pointers
  + [table_status] is seed
  + [table_scope] is active faculty attention and periphery inquiry surfaces
  + [authority_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop
  + [entry_count] is 14
  + [coverage_status] is partial and intentionally non-exhaustive
  + [residual_outside] is unindexed SOP files, stale historical F:\.sop references, runtime pointers, and terms not yet reviewed

  = must: support lookup by surface_key and inquiry_term
  = must: preserve candidate status until the target file is actually inspected
  = must: be updated when a surface marker adds lookup-ready terms
  - never: treat this table as complete coverage of the repository

& [SurfaceMarker_UnifiedFacultyAttention] is the table surface for unified faculty attention
  + [surface_key] is unified_faculty_attention
  + [surface_file] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\UnifiedFacultyAttention.sop
  + [inquiry_term_set] is depth_profile, faculty_field, balance_axis_set, shared_pair_frame, direction_integration_axis, unified_interrogation_cycle, depth_weighted_activation, wisdom_caution_axis, periphery_state, semantic_lookup, semantic_hash_index, traversal, latent_depth, periphery_dimensional_probe, unresolved_faculty_residual, and router
  + [lookup_status] is lookup_ready

& [SurfaceMarker_SectionedPeripheryAssociationFabric] is the table surface for sectioned periphery association
  + [surface_key] is sectioned_periphery_association_fabric
  + [surface_file] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SectionedPeripheryAssociationFabric.sop
  + [inquiry_term_set] is internal_periphery_section, external_periphery_section, primary_document_association, secondary_document_association, internal_consistency_stability, external_model_stability, and triangulation_weight
  + [lookup_status] is lookup_ready

